This paper discusses the impact of network densification on wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the impact of network densification on network capacity, which involves information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions interference management, which is related to multimedia systems and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. The paper also discusses possible approaches to enhance network capacity, which involves system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and future directions, which involves security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category.
